-- Hong Kong H-share index soars to highest close in 2014
-- By Grace Li
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 04:08AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, July 23 (Reuters) - An index of major China companies listed in Hong Kong on Wednesday surged to its highest close this year, as investors piled into financial and energy stocks seen as undervalued.

The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> climbed 2 percent to close at its highest since Dec. 27, while the benchmark Hang Seng Index <.HSI> was up 0.8 percent at 23,971.87 points, its highest since Dec. 2. Daily bourse volume was the heaviest since April 11.  Chinese property stocks were top percentage gainers on the Hang Seng for a second day, with China Resources Land <1109.HK> jumping 7.5 percent and China Overseas Land & Investment <0688.HK> up 4.4 percent. The 21st Century Business Herald reported late on Tuesday around 10 more Chinese cities are expected to relax home-purchase restrictions under the pressure of high inventories.